# Plan: Add "mistral-instruct-v3" Chat Template Handler

## Context

Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 uses a simpler instruction format than the existing Ministral 3 handler. The Ministral 3 handler (`common_chat_params_init_ministral_3`) targets the newer Ministral/Magistral Large 3 models which use `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, `[TOOL_CALLS]`, `[ARGS]` markers and PEG-based parsing. In contrast, the older Mistral Instruct v0.3 format uses plain `[INST]`/`[/INST]` delimiters without `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, and needs no tool-calling or PEG grammar support — just simple prompt string construction.

## File to Modify

- **`common/chat.cpp`** — add handler function + detection logic (only file modified)
- **`common/chat.h`** — NOT modified (uses existing `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY`)

## Step 1: Add the Handler Function

**Location:** After `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3` (which ends around line 1491+), before the helper functions that follow.

Add a new static function:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string prompt = "<s>";
    std::string system_message;

    // First pass: extract system message if present
    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role = msg.value("role", "");
        if (role == "system") {
            system_message = msg.value("content", "");
            break;  // only first system message
        }
    }

    bool first_user = true;
    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            // System message handled by prepending to first user turn
            continue;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user && !system_message.empty()) {
                prompt += "[INST] " + system_message + "\n" + content + " [/INST]";
            } else {
                prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
            first_user = false;
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            prompt += content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.prompt = prompt;
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;

    return data;
}
```

**Key design decisions:**
- System message is prepended to the first user message with a `\n` separator (matching the Mistral v0.3 format spec)
- Uses `msg.value("role", "")` and `msg.value("content", "")` — same pattern as existing handlers
- Sets `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` (no PEG grammar needed — this is a simple text-only template)
- `<s>` BOS token starts the prompt; `</s>` EOS token follows each assistant turn

## Step 2: Register in Detection Function

**Location:** In `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (line 1634), add a new detection block just before the final `return std::nullopt;` (line 1690).

